If I could give this establishment zero stars, I would. As a restaurant worker, I am sad to say that this was the absolute worst service experience of my life. Two friends and I were in town for the Women's March, and after rallying and marching all day, we found this place close to where we were staying. We were seated at 7:20 and ordered immediately as we had been looking at the menu while we waited for a table (~5-10 minutes). We ordered one appetizer and 3 pad thai. We waited for a full hour and a half and we got our pad thai at 8:50. Our appetizer never arrived. During the hour and a half wait, no one checked on us, apologized for the delay, or brought us anything to eat. The restaurant was very busy, clearly more than they are used to, because of the march. As a restaurant worker I know that when your kitchen is backed up and people are waiting too long for their food, you should slow down. This place did no such thing. They continued to seat people as soon as tables opened, and they were taking insane amounts of takeout orders as well. So, while half of the restaurant was waiting an hour and a half for their food (the tables on either side of us were seated at the same time and got their food at the same time as us), other people who arrived after us were seated, served, paid, and left before we got our meal, and we saw many people pick up takeout orders while we were waiting. The pad thai was okay, and when we got the bill I asked to speak with a manager. A girl came over and said that she was in charge. I politely told her about our experience and let her know that I didn't want to pay for the meal, as the service was completely inexcusable. She apologized and said she had to speak to her boss (I don't know why they wouldn't just send him over in the first place). A man came to our table and belligerently told us that we shouldn't have eaten his food if we didn't want to pay for it. I re-explained the experience that we had and let him know that I didn't believe our experience was worth any amount of money, and of course we ate the food considering we waited an hour and a half for it. He started to yell at us and said "why did you eat my food" repeatedly, told us that EVERYBODY was waiting (isn't that worse?) then finally told us to just leave and said that we should go home and think about what we've done.  All three of us work in restaurants and agreed that the level of service we received was inexcusable. While we are entirely sympathetic to the difficulties of a busy night, if any of us were to treat our guests the way that we were treated tonight, especially when the problems that we experienced could have easily been remedied (slowing down/not seating so many people at once, sending a complimentary appetizer while we waited, or even just apologizing for the wait), we would be fired. While the food was okay, I would not dine at this establishment considering the level of service and the way that we were treated by the manager/possibly owner.

Aroi is a hidden gem in a town full of bad Thai restaurants.  Not only was take out service quick, like 5 minutes quick, the servers were attentive and courteous.  I ordered the drunken noodles which came out perfectly seasoned and chewy.  No noodles were clumped or dry.  In fact, these were the best drunken noodles I have had in a while.  I definitely plan on coming back here to try their other plates, and might be willing to raise my rating to 5 stars if the consistency remains solid.

The service is usually lovely and the food is excellent. They had someone new serving Monday night and she rushed us out of the restaurant before we could finish enjoying our food. It was 9:30 and mentioned the kitchen closes at 10. I work in a restaurant as well, just because the kitchen closes does not mean you rush your customers out. People were still walking in at 9:45 and the bordering restaurants were packed - we probably should have went to one of them instead. Won't be back to Aroi for a while...

From the sushi to the pad thai, you will love everything offered at this great Thai restaurant.  It's never over-crowded when I've been which I love.  I don't mind waiting for this great food...but glad that most seem to order delivery; which by the way is always fast and the food is always hot. I love the sushi here along with the calamari.  The entrees are also good and I'm a fan of the cashew chicken and the basil fried rice.  Glad to have something so good to my place.

Aroi Thai is a fantastic neighborhood spot. Food is very good, served quickly, piping hot, and always fresh. Curries are flavorful and bright, noodles are perfectly done, most dishes have the proper heat and tang factor. Service is lovely. A nice option for either dine-in (better yet, dine al fresco on a nice day) or take-out/delivery on a mellow night. A welcome addition to the neighborhood.
